combined_ragas: Miyan ki malhar, Malhar ki prakar
empty_tradition: Miyan ki malhar, Malhar ki prakar

structural_equivalents.relationship: Same scale (Lydian mode with tivra Ma)
structural_equivalents.notes: Both use Lydian mode. Differences are stylistic (gamaka in Carnatic, Re/Pa treatment in Hindustani)
Both use Major/Ionian scale. Very close equivalents.
Both use S R2 G3 P D2 S. Practically identical.

mood_equivalents.notes: Carnatic Bhairavi = janya of Natabhairavi, Hindustani Bhairavi = Bhairavi thaat (all komal swaras). Different structures, both evoke pathos/devotion.
Carnatic Todi uses R1 G2 M1 D1 N2, Hindustani Todi uses komal Re, Ga, Dha, Ni with tivra Ma. Emotional overlap but different swaras.
Both are pentatonic, but Hindolam = S G2 M1 D1 N2; Malkauns = S g M d n. Different note sets, similar introspective/serious mood.
